✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: The statement is very clear and fun, cases are different and good. Great clash !

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Great clash, the conditions are simple, but they still keep the clash tricky (such as the number formatting). Validators are pretty solid too. Took me like 7-8 minutes but that may be due to lack of skill mostly.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Fun challenge: while it is a challenge that requires a couple of steps rather than one line, the statement is clear enough to keep it a coding challenge.
I hope you received enough feedback from the community to improve your contribution. Once you have made the necessary updates, publish your contribution!

Interesting idea.

Goal
* Please mention there is no floor {{0}}.

Constraints
* Please fix the second constraint, as some of the cases violate it.

Other thoughts:

For Fastest mode it should be relatively straightforward to use either some string functions or a regex to solve the puzzle. For Shortest mode the clash will definitely require much more thought.

To make the output prettier, you may request the player to right-align both columns and add extra spaces in front of the numbers where necessary, e.g.

(requires monospace formatting)
```
100 101
 98  99
…
 11  12
  9  10
…
 -1   1
 -3  -2
…
-10  -9
-12 -11
```

Of course, that additional requirement would add some more time needed to think it out.

Thanks.

Thought this could be a fun clash idea since it's complex enough to take some thought, but still pretty easy to solve in 5-10 minutes.

My later test cases are a pretty absurd for any skyscraper, but I figured it's better to test the code well than to be 'realistic'. For reference the most above ground floors in any building is 163 for the Burj Khalifa and the most underground floors seems to be 12 for the Sydney Opera House.
Flat-earthers might consider the 100 floors of the Australia 108 building to be all underground.

Thanks as always, implemented the simple changes.

As for the formatting change, I would rather keep it simple. I find clashers often getting 0% on clashes that have too much formatting involved, so I'd rather they just focus on the core challenge for this one. :)
